  --- README.md
  Conscrypt - A Java Security Provider
  Conscrypt is a Java Security Provider (JSP) that implements parts of the Java
  #### Uber JAR
  For convenience, we also publish an Uber JAR to Maven Central that contains the shared
  To depend on the uber jar, simply use the `conscrypt-openjdk-uber` artifacts.
  --- CAPABILITIES.md
  providers, including the ones bundled with OpenJDK, which always use SHA-1 for the MGF1 digest.
  --- BUILDING.md
  --- openjdk/src/main/java/org/conscrypt/NativeLibraryLoader.java
      private static final String WORK_DIR_PROPERTY_NAME = "org.conscrypt.native.workdir";
  --- openjdk/src/main/java/org/conscrypt/HostProperties.java
      private static final String TEMP_DIR_PROPERTY_NAME = "org.conscrypt.tmpdir";
              // Use the Java system property if available.
              f = toDirectory(System.getProperty("java.io.tmpdir"));
                  f = toDirectory(System.getenv("TMPDIR"));
